Using a <TOOL>hex screwdriver</TOOL>, <OPER>unscrew</OPER> the 2 <PROP>long</PROP> <PART>bolts</PART> that go <RPOS>through</RPOS> the <PART>starter motor</PART>.
Later on, <OPER>unscrew</OPER> the 2 <RPOS>top</RPOS> <PART>screws</PART> with a <TOOL>Phillips screwdriver</TOOL>.
Then, <OPER>remove</OPER> the <PART>cover cap</PART> and <PART>commutator end cover</PART>, <OPER>disconnect</OPER> the <PART>main braided cable</PART> from the <PART>threaded terminal</PART> and <OPER>remove</OPER> the <PROP>cylindrical</PROP> <PART>housing</PART>.
After that, <OPER>unscrew</OPER> the 3 <PART>mounting screws</PART> on the <RPOS>lower</RPOS> section of the <PART>starter motor</PART> using a <TOOL>star screwdriver</TOOL> (Torx).
Finally, <OPER>remove</OPER> the <PART>solenoid</PART>.
